item.title: Different severs
item.dc:creator: @Eportal Eportal
item.description:
@Eportal wrote:

noob12345678:

once you are on the moparscape clientscreen. click help. then click server status page .search for a scape that you would want to go on. copy the ip adress and port. then log in

In noobier words: Once you are at the moparscape webclient, click on server stats page at the top of the screen and search for a server that you would like to go to, now copy that server by server I mean something that will look like 5.432.209.114 or example.no-ip.org. Now once you have copied one op thoes servers, go back to the webclient and click files then click new server then press CTR+V and press ok. now go back to the server status page and you will see a thing that says “port” copy the server that you selecteds port and click on file, new port and past the port then “ok” and lig in, type a username or pass and you are ready to roll. If it says “error connection go server, must be down” then the server is offline AKA “down”. A port is a 5 digit number, the default port is 43594. Hope this helped!
